docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  docs/RELATIONSHIP_GRAPH.md,project,"public event,snapshot,analytics,and graph-context contracts"
body: "## Matrix axes\n\nScale; graph topology; edge-kind family; history age; mutation concurrency; index state; query budget; adapter; serialization; schema version; failure injection; permissions or redaction; exact versus approximate algorithm.\n\n## Required adversarial cases\n\nDense cliques; long chains; wide stars; duplicate aliases; associative cycles; genuine ordering cycles; dangling imported endpoints; self-links; contradictory inverses; high-degree hubs; temporal supersession; checkpoint corruption; concurrent retyping; stale cursors; severe token limits.\n\n## Reporting\n\nDefault CI output is a compact pass or fail envelope with deltas. Full evidence is stored as artifacts or linked results and remains available by case, seed, snapshot, and scale. No benchmark may silently skip or downscale."
